and convergent thinking,

00:01:27.520 --> 00:01:30.580
and to drive towards
a targeted outcome.

00:01:30.580 --> 00:01:32.770
So what's different
about a design sprint

00:01:32.770 --> 00:01:37.030
is that we set clear goals
and deliverables upfront.

00:01:37.030 --> 00:01:39.310
We time box all
of the activities

00:01:39.310 --> 00:01:41.980
so that we not only speed up
the learning and development

00:01:41.980 --> 00:01:46.600
process, but we also drive the
right behaviors from our users.

00:01:46.600 --> 00:01:50.110
And then finally, we enable
a wide range of disciplines

00:01:50.110 --> 00:01:53.440
and stakeholders to participate
in the design and development

00:01:53.440 --> 00:01:56.090
process.

00:01:56.090 --> 00:01:58.690
Now, design is not
an individual sport.

00:01:58.690 --> 00:02:02.200
And design sprints are a
highly collaborative process.

00:02:02.200 --> 00:02:05.440
We want to be able to
include multiple perspectives

00:02:05.440 --> 00:02:07.030
and points of views.

00:02:07.030 --> 00:02:09.009
And to that end,
we leverage sprints

00:02:09.009 --> 00:02:13.540
to include all
participant's voices.

00:02:13.540 --> 00:02:16.780
