a couple of exercises

00:04:42.150 --> 00:04:44.730
that are designed to get the
ideas out of your participant's

00:04:44.730 --> 00:04:47.700
head onto paper, and
to really push them

00:04:47.700 --> 00:04:50.940
to go beyond their first idea to
get better and more innovative

00:04:50.940 --> 00:04:53.130
ideas.

00:04:53.130 --> 00:04:55.230
Now, once we have
all of these ideas

00:04:55.230 --> 00:04:57.150
and we're in the
middle of a sprint,

00:04:57.150 --> 00:04:59.280
we have tons and tons
of solutions, it's time

00:04:59.280 --> 00:05:02.880
to start narrowing down
and making hard choices.

00:05:02.880 --> 00:05:05.820
So the decide phase is all
about those hard decisions

00:05:05.820 --> 00:05:10.210
and selecting what you're
going to prototype with users.

00:05:10.210 --> 00:05:12.100
Once you've narrowed
down, you want

00:05:12.100 --> 00:05:15.080
to create a prototype that
you can test your hypothesis

00:05:15.080 --> 00:05:18.580
and validate or invalidate
your assumptions.

00:05:18.580 --> 00:05:20.860
Because you only have a
really short amount of time,

00:05:20.860 --> 00:05:22.960
maybe you have a
couple hours, maybe you

00:05:22.960 --> 00:05:25.790
have a day to build
that prototype,

00:05:25.790 --> 00:05:27.700
it should only be
as high fidelity as

00:05:27.700 --> 00:05:30.610
needed to answer your
questions, and nothing more.

00:05:33.180 --> 00:05:35.160
Finally, we're
going to validate.

00:05:35.160 --> 00:05:37.320
The goal of the test
phase is to confirm

00:05:37.320 --> 00:05:39.060
that the product that
you have prototyped

00:05:39.060 --> 00:05:43.360
is good, and also, that you
prototyped the right thing.

00:05:43.360 --> 00:05:46.530
