bringing it to empathy.

00:10:17.746 --> 00:10:19.120
And this is when
you are actually

00:10:19.120 --> 00:10:21.970
stepping into someone's
shoes and experiencing

00:10:21.970 --> 00:10:23.530
what they experience.

00:10:23.530 --> 00:10:26.710
Understanding their
needs, their pain points,

00:10:26.710 --> 00:10:30.610
their hopes and dreams, and
even things that delight them.

00:10:30.610 --> 00:10:34.780
So when you have awareness,
listening, empathy,

00:10:34.780 --> 00:10:36.630
all of these three
things together,

00:10:36.630 --> 00:10:39.250
that's going to be
considered immersion.

00:10:39.250 --> 00:10:44.740
So how does this relate to
design sprints and design?

00:10:44.740 --> 00:10:48.250
Now, when you're in a design
sprint, you are making a call,

00:10:48.250 --> 00:10:51.280
and you are designing
solutions for users

00:10:51.280 --> 00:10:54.190
based on what you think is
going to work well for them.

00:10:54.190 --> 00:10:56.060
Now, where does this come from?

00:10:56.060 --> 00:10:59.440
It comes from intuition.

00:10:59.440 --> 00:11:01.780
And how does
intuition get built?

00:11:01.780 --> 00:11:04.600
It comes from a
lifetime of experience.

00:11:04.600 --> 00:11:07.270
It comes from
knowledge and study.

00:11:07.270 --> 00:11:10.120
It comes from trial and
error, like launching

00:11:10.120 --> 00:11:12.340
a lot of designs, and
seeing what works,

00:11:12.340 --> 00:11:14.890
and learning from success,
learning from failure.

00:11:14.890 --> 00:11:18.480
It's a constant loop of
learning and tweaking.

00:11:18.480 --> 00:11:20.200
But when you're
designing for users

00:11:20.200 --> 00:11:22.960
that you've never
interacted with before,

00:11:22.960 --> 00:11:25.240
you don't have this intuition.

00:11:25.240 --> 00:11:27.610
So what happens in the
context of a sprint?

00:11:27.610 --> 00:11:30.190
All of this gets amplified.

00:11:30.190 --> 00:11:33.610
In a sprint, you're time-boxed,
so you're doing things really

00:11:33.610 --> 00:11:35.260
fast.

00:11:35.260 --> 00:11:37.690
It's a high pressure situation.

00:11:37.690 --> 00:11:40.120
It's not just you,
but probably you

00:11:40.120 --> 00:11:43.000
and a bunch of sprinters who
are all in the same boat as you.

00:11:43.000 --> 00:11:45.580
You don't understand
your user really well.

00:11:45.580 --> 00:11:49.000
So Burgan and I are often
placed in situations like this

00:11:49.000 --> 00:11:51.270
because we both work
on products where

00:11:51.270 --> 00:11:52.990
